<Content>Noisy We stayed here for only one night as the next day we fly back home. We paid $56 US for the night including breakfast. For the price, the location was great, a few blocks away from the Zocalo and Catedral. The rooms are a little small and a bit dark but for one night it was okay. The bathroom didn鈥檛 have a divider so you cannot use it while someone is showering or you will get wet.Our main concern was that we couldn鈥檛 sleep due to the noise on the first floor. It was echoing and bouncing back on the four walls that the window was facing. We were hearing everything from people talking loud, singing loud, shouting, etc. At 2 am, we had to call the front desk to see if they can check what was going on and maybe get them to keep it low. It took maybe about 15-20 min for the noise to subside. After that we were able to sleep or we just got tired. 
