<Author>TodW
<Content>A Very Adequate Hotel at a good location and price I arrived at The Hotel Canada after my confirmed room at the Hotel Catedral was sold to someone else. The staff were welcoming. The room was small but reasonably equipped with door chain, bed, wardrobe, bedside light, safe and ensuite lavatory and shower. You have 30 min a day free use of the Holiday Inn internet along the road. For a traveller on a budget it was fine. I paid a bit under USD50 for BB the first night, rather less when I returned for a further 2 nights. The hotel is located near the Cathedral in the square (Zocalo) on Calle 5 Mayo, a block further on from the Zocalo Holiday Inn who owns this hotel. An excellent location for exploring the historic area. 
