<Author>A TripAdvisor Member
<Content>clean, friendly, great location I am in Mexico quite ofter during the year and have been staying at the Hotel Canada for the past ten years of visits.The staff is friendly, full of information, most of the staff speaks at least some English and are more than willing to help in any way possible to make ones visit to the city a good one.There is a tourist desk located in the hotel that can fix you up with day trips, or longer ones if you desire, at resonable cost.It is an older hotel but has been kept up and is always clean and bright, some of the front rooms do catch some of the traffic noise from the street but not enough to really matter.The rates are great and it is close to many of the major attractions in the city. 
